Milestones:
+ 1. Need to refactor task column switch. There're many questions: should I
     add builtin columns, can it be moved to plugin, etc.
     Decided: plugin, not core (see Ideas #7). Keeps core minimal - columns,
     transitions, board rendering all live in a (first-party) plugin. Only
     real core dependency is giving `ls` hook support (`cli/ls.c:166`, already
     flagged there); without it a plugin can annotate `tec cat` via
     `hook_cat` but has no way to group/filter/render `tec ls`.
  2. Command to list task needs brainstorming as well.
  3. How to implement workflow engine. Yeah, there is such thing.
  4. How to add support for multi-users. Will it break existing code


Priorities:
  high - bugfix, hotfix and feature tasks.
  mid  - constant stuff like make it faster, smaller, etc.
  low  - when you get time


Bugs:
+ 1. Command `tec col prev <TASKID>` moves task to column 'prev' even if no current task ID is set.
+ 2. Command `tec move` can't move multiple task to another environment.
+ 3. Command `tec move` cant move 2 task to destination. It simply renames it.
+ 4. Command `tec set -d 'description'` causes malloc fail, when set longer
     description than before.
  5. NULL-termination should follow `strncpy(dst, src, len)`. In case `src`
     is equal to `len` it'll end without '\0'. Checked it with valgrind.
  6. Command `tec move` does not work after adding new feature to support desks.
+ 7. `tec cd taskID1 taskID2` doesn't set previous toggle.
+ 8. If current or previous task is moved to done, update desk toggles.
  9. `tec env add <env>` causes desk description duplicated cuz they both use ctx->units.
 10. `hook_show` does not return proper return code. Mabye popen() is problem.


Ideas:
  1. Replace cat & ls hooks with reading from file. Gonna highly optimize
     command exection.
  2. Add multiple users.
  3. Add support for plugin to use libtec/tec commands.
+ 4. Add support to pass system config values via option to util.
+ 5. Add option to show task columns in command `tec col`.
+ 6. Add plugin `note` to take notes. Synopsis: tec note [OPTION]... COMMAND
  7. Add plugin workflow to move task from columns to column. See Milestone
     #1: decided to keep this fully in a plugin, not core. Plugin owns column
     names/transitions/board rendering and reads/writes the task's
     `.tec/units` file directly (stable `key : val` format, `lib/path.c`) -
     no new unit key or `set` flag needed in core. `ls` renders one row per
     task though (unlike `cat`'s one task per call), so a naive per-row
     `hook_cat`-style popen would add N subprocess spawns to a command
     that's already flagged as too slow (see Prio: low #3). Plan: plugin
     uses threads (pthreads, see idea #26) to query/print rows in parallel
     instead of a single batched call.
+ 8. Add libtec NOT as submodule but dependency
  9. Use command `gh` to generate releases
+10. Unify environment/desk/task's unit and column modules.
 11. Add config option to enable/disable desk support in environment.
 12. Add commands export/import to move tasks in and out of desks.
+13. Add short list of exit statuses, other than libtec provides.
+14. Add support for command 'tec sync -n', to add task to curr column, but not change to task directory
 15. Make ID generatation bigger than the last ID. Might run outta IDs, but just think about it.
 16. Add support for mark into `tec list`. For builtin and custom columns
 17. Add task directory option for command `tec init [DIR]`. If nothing's passed use value from config file.
     If nothing found in there then use current directory
 18. Add errstr along with errno. It'l be used to specify invalid input argument or something
 19. Rename module 'unit' to linked list in lib part.
 20. Add support to unit module not to change file content if new data is the same as old ones.
+21. Prevent column update when new column name is the same as old. Same about units
 22. Add pager like in git. Add option --no-pager to turn pager feature off. like in git.
+24. Maybe let command `set' let not to take any values to change? In that case change nothing.
 25. Add support for plugins to be called from $PATH like git does. `tec-pgnname` files should be called as plugin as well
 26. Use pthreads to parse plugin output
 27. Add fuzzy picker (fzf-style) for `tec cd`/`tec ls` to interactively select
     task/desk/env. Core pitch of tec is fewest keystrokes; picking by exact ID
     doesn't scale once there're more than a handful of tasks.
 28. Add support for `tec cd -N` to jump back N switches, not just one. Toggle
     module currently only tracks curr/prev (two slots), would need a small
     history stack instead.
 29. Add frecency-based ordering in `tec ls` (most-used/most-recent first).
     Needs a last-accessed timestamp per task, similar to how `add` already
     stores a creation date in units.
 30. Add tags/labels for tasks, independent of env/desk hierarchy. Support
     `tec ls --tag <tag>` to search across envs/desks without moving anything.
 31. Add archive state for tasks so `tec rm` doesn't hard-delete. Right now
     `tec_task_rm()` (lib/libtec.c) -> `dir_task_rm()` -> lib/osdep.c runs
     `rm -rf` on the whole task dir, notes/sketches included, unrecoverable.
     Instead move it to `$TASKDIR/.trash/<env>/<desk>/<id>-<timestamp>/`, add
     `tec rm --purge` (or age/size-based sweep) to actually reclaim space.
 32. Show task creation date in `tec ls` output. `cli/add.c` (generate_units)
     already stores a "date" unit on every `add`, it's just never displayed.
 33. Add command `tec stats` to show counts per env/desk/column and oldest
     open tasks, using unit data already on disk, no new storage needed.
 34. Show git branch/status inline in `tec ls` via existing show hook.
     `hooks.show` in tec.cfg already wires e.g. `gmux show` to per-task
     display, just needs a column in `ls` output.
 35. Add `--json` output option for `ls`/`cat` for scripting, e.g. piping
     into `jq`/`fzf`/other plugins.
 36. Add plugin for time tracking (start/stop timer per task), same shape as
     the existing `gmux`/`nine`/`find` plugins.
 37. Add `tec restore <id>` to bring a task back from the trash before purge
     (undo companion to idea 31).
 38. Add command `tec cfg check` to validate config file and that
     `base.pgn`/`base.task` directories actually exist, so bad config fails
     fast with a clear message instead of obscurely later.


